subsection.def:
action
                    (訴訟) includes suit, counterclaim, and
                set-off;

buyer
                    (買方) means a person who buys or agrees to buy
                goods;

delivery
                    (交、交付)
                means voluntary transfer of possession from one person to another;

plaintiff
                    (原告人) includes a defendant
                counterclaiming;

property
                    (產權) means the general property in goods, and
                not merely a special property;

sale
                    (售賣) includes a bargain and sale as well as a
                sale and delivery;

seller
                    (賣方) means a person who sells or agrees to
                sell goods;

subparagraph.content:
in a case where the parties to the contract intend that the seller
                        should transfer only such title as a third person may have, that person;
                        nor
